[0m[49m[39m  360, 376[0m:[39m[49m 
[0m[49m[39m  361, 377[0m:[39m[49m **Step 5: Store and expose results.** Every classification, whether it triggered an alert or not, is stored in Timestream for retrospective analysis. This enables clinicians to review a patient's waveform analysis history ("show me all rhythm classifications for this patient over the last 24 hours"), supports model performance monitoring (tracking false positive rates over time), and provides the training data for model improvement. The storage layer also feeds dashboards that show unit-level alert rates, signal quality trends, and system health metrics.
